@danialfarid I use this plugin on a site where user submits images using a mobile device. The problem is that on mobile devices the network connection to the backend server will be down occasionally but the user should be all the time able to continue taking pictures an putting those on queue for uploading them to the backend server when the connection is again working.

My approach to solve this issue was to try to send the data again and again until the backend server has recieved the complete file. As I tested the code linked above I noticed that this plugin itself creates a lot of errors when the server can't be reached and it somehow messes up the data that was being uploaded so that a new try is not anymore possible (unlike when using $http).

What would be the correct way to detect transfer errors for this plugin?

