Whilst the solution proposed in bc92416 is correct, it is also clearly problematic on Windows.

@wulmer - could you try timing Tempfile usage on a directory you don't have access to on Windows? My assumption is that the performance is disastrous, and fundamentally is a Tempfile issue. Assuming that to be the case, do you know if that is documented somewhere or even an issue on the Python tracker?

Even so, we are going to have to find a solution to this. It might make sense to have a different code path for Windows where we inspect the filesystem for writability, rather than asking forgiveness if we can't write to the desired location.

