`rs2::frameset` provides several ways of getting a specific frame from it.

1.  Iterating over it a querying the type of stream per frame.
```cpp
rs2::frameset frames = pipe.wait_for_frames();
for(auto&& f : frames)
{
    if(f.get_profile().stream_type() == RS2_STREAM_INFRARED)
    {
        \\f is an infrared frame
    }
}
```

2. Using the `rs2::frameset::first(rs_stream s)` method:
https://github.com/IntelRealSense/librealsense/blob/67cdafef0c79554cd0c482d188f76feffd1bd9e2/include/librealsense2/hpp/rs_frame.hpp#L483
For example:
```cpp
rs2::frameset frames = pipe.wait_for_frames();
rs2::frame ir_frame = frames.first(RS2_STREAM_INFRARED);
```

